FBIS3-58391 "drweu008aa_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 January 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS French Leaders Comment on Bosnia Situation, Summit Mitterrand: UN's Duty To Ensure Safety LD1101205794 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 1900 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101205794 Paris France-2 Television Network Language: French Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] This time the threat seems more serious than before: NATO is envisaging launching air strikes on Serb positions if the Serbs continue to block humanitarian assistance. [passage omitted] It now remains to be seen whether the signal from Brussels will be persuasive enough for the belligerents to change their attitude: [Begin Francois Mitterrand recording] We cannot count on the goodwill alone of the three parties to the conflict -- Serbs, Croats, and Bosnian Muslims. It seems to us simply that the first duty of the UN forces is to ensure the safety of their comrades involved in peace missions. [end recording] [passage omitted]
